rComments: A great prof overall! I took this class as an elective and it was an interesting class. The format was online but the prof managed to make the class great. Although, the final was 100 MCQ which I found a little excessive even if we had plenty of time to finish it. I wouldn't have done such a final but besides that, I enjoyed the class very much!

Because the classes were online, there were no real "classes," the required work was reading the textbook, and before every test, she made a video outlining what was essential to know to do well. She explains difficult concepts in a very easily understandable way. I would recommend her if you want an easy, interesting class.

By far the best prof ever! She's so sweet and considerate of the situation we're in at the moment. She explains every concept very well and she's really straightforward. She always let's us know of key elements to study for the quizzes and exams and whether something will or will not be on the exam. I really enjoyed this class with her!!
Great teacher for online!

She is by far my favorite prof. She cares about the success of her students. She gives good examples and is entertaining. There is a lot of reading to do in this class, all of it being mandatory but if you like psychology, it gets done pretty fast. The tests are easy to do as well if you studied enough.

The best teacher I had this semester. her video before the quiz are really helpful and shes telling you the key point of the exam which is really nice considering chapter are over 80 pages each and quizzes usually cover 2 chapters.
Very kind prof. Everything is clear and understandable. She makes great review videos before tests.
Shes really nice

This prof is so sweet and cute! Had to do the whole class on TopHat because of COVID so there's a lot of reading but there's little questions throughout that make it more interesting. She also posts videos of her explaining each chapter for clear review and adds funny examples. The quizzes are clear and directly related to the class content.

J'adore cette prof. Elle est très clair dans ses attentes et elle enseigne vraiment bien. Les lectures sont intéressantes, et toutes les notes sont sur Brightspace. J'aimerais bien suivre un autre de ses cours.
Elle est une professeure merveilleuse. Elle est respectueuse avec les etudiants et nous prepare bien aux examens. Je la reprendrai si elle enseigne un autre cours.

ABSOLUTELY AMAZING PROF! She teaches the material with many exampleS to help further your understanding, and in a manner that inspires one to learn. Also, she is very clear on the content that will appear on the exams. I would love to take another class with her if I could.
She's so sweet!! Super nice and accessible if you have any questions after class
Tres bonne professeure.

This prof is the best! She is my favorite prof because she gives great examples of the material being taught. It's so nice to have a prof that's actually genuienly caring towards students. Would 100% recommend her to anyone!
Professeure magnifique! Si elle enseignait d'autres cours à l'université je m'inscrirais immédiatement. C'est un prof qui veut voir ses élèves réussir.

Favourite teacher! She has an amazing energy even if her class is at 8:30 am. She makes you want to learn and to surpass your abilities. She has good examples for every concepts she teaches. Would 110% recommend her to anyone.

She explain perfectly the subject, shes so caring she wants everyone to sucess so she make sure everybody understands, give alot of her time and she gives alot of examples wich really helped me and before each class we do a quizz to make sure we undertsand what we did last class. Shes is literally the best teacher I had since I started Uni!!

Super sweet prof. Would start every class with a kahoot on material learned from the previous class. Exams mostly based on PowerPoint slide and would use questions from her kahoots. Also gave us 3 bonus questions on each midterm!

The midterms are entirely based on the power points. Easy A for those. The final is harder because the faculty makes it and it is entirely based on the textbook. Over all her class is easy, very good prof.

She's great! Very nice and caring lady. She gave good straight forward tests that were easy to study for. No surprises on her midterms if you study the slides you'll be able to get easy A's without any problem. You don't need to use the textbook but its a common exam for all psych classes so its based off of it. I did fine without it though.

She is one of the most caring and accessible profs out there and always takes time to answer all students' questions during her lectures. The quizzes at the beginning of class are good practice for the midterms and exam which were all quite easy.

This prof was kind and sweet. I really loved her class. She reminds you of the important stuff by having pop quizzes at the beginning of every class which made things fun and entertaining. She is funny, knowledgable, accessible outside of class and wants everybody to succeed. She puts all the notes on Brightspace too! Would highly recommend!

For immersion students she speaks very quickly and high pitched which can be tricky to understand. Very caring prof. Posts lectures so you don't even have to go to class although I'd recommend going to the review sessions. Exam is textbook based so be sure to read the stuff in the textbook thats noted on the lecture slides.

She is a really kind teacher. You get 4% just by doing a couple of surveys. She has three quizzes that are super easy and two midterms based on her slide shows however if you want to do really good I suggest reading the book as well. The final exam is 100% textbook related so DO NOT fall behind on reading or you WILL regret it
Soooooo kind, caring! she will give her time to you no matter what, she is super comprehensible, and guides you for midterms and finals.

She was not boring once all semester. she posts everything online but going to class helps because she has examples for everything. Midterms are pretty easy and mostly based on her lecture but the final is 100% on the textbook. She's easy to reach for any questions and will answer questions from the previous class and have a quiz on it. 11/10!

She is very nice. she posts all her lectures online and goes over them in class with a little extra detail. her midterms are really easy but you should study to do well. the midterms are based on the lectures and the final based completely on the textbook, which I did not like very much since that is the only time you the textbook
